==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iris diaphragm
<hw>I"ris di"a*phragm</hw>. <def>An adjustable diaphragm, reminiscent of
the iris of the eye in its action, by which the diameter of an
approximately circular opening may be controlled, as for regulating the
aperture of a lens; it consists of a number of movable thin curved
plates fastened at regular intervals around the inside of a ring, the
positions of which are simultaneously adjusted by a single knob on the
outside of the lens. It is used in cameras and microscopes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irised</ent>⟦br⟧
